<Base title="Quarry — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/quarry/">← Quarry</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 6, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Quarry does not track how you use the app. Your database contents and query results stay on your Mac unless you connect to database servers you configure.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Quarry opens local files and remote databases at your request. We do not receive your database contents, query text, schema, exports, or connection history.</p>

  <h2>Credentials</h2>
  <p>Saved passwords are stored in the macOS Keychain. You can remove saved credentials from Keychain Access or from Quarry's connection settings.</p>

  <h2>Purchases and licenses</h2>
  <p>If Quarry offers a paid unlock, payment and license validation may use the provider details needed to complete that purchase. We never receive your database data through licensing.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/quarry/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
